	<comments>http://www.sermonaudio.com/new_details3.asp?ID=28312#comments</comments>
	<author>Reformation Church</author>
	<description>Former Roman priest Richard Bennett &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.BereanBeacon.org&quot;&gt;(www.BereanBeacon.org&lt;/a&gt;) and Pastor Mencarow have made TWO new videos: &quot;The Original Early Church&quot; and &quot;Reformation To Modern Times.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;THE ORIGINAL EARLY CHURCH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The topic of who the early believers were, where they lived, and just  what they taught is very important. We have great examples as the  Vaudois (Waldenses) to the pre-Reformation believers. In this video Pastor W. J. Mencarow and Richard Bennett clearly document the actual  historical facts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is imperative to analyze the details of the  historical records. This is professionally done in the video with graphics,  maps and paintings that illustrate these facts and make them easily  understood. Believers are urged to research and see for themselves that  what is shown is indeed the authentic early church. Kindly make it known  to others by forwarding its URL others.  Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J8BjmtC8_ps&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt; &quot;The Original Early Church&quot;  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J8BjmtC8_ps&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;REFORMATION TO MODERN TIMES&lt;br /&gt;History is of supreme importance as it is the storehouse of lessons comprehended from the past. In this DVD Pastor W. J. Mencarow along with Richard Bennett clearly documents the actual historical facts of following the Reformation. Since the Papacy has not only attempted to reverse the influence of the Reformation, but also to rewrite history, it is imperative to know the established facts of history. This is professionally accomplished in this DVD. Photographs, paintings, and maps illustrate historical facts, making them more easily understood. Kindly make the DVD known to others by forwarding its URL. Thank you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://bit.ly/rdcGdQ&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&quot;Reformation To Modern Times&quot; http://bit.ly/rdcGdQ&lt;/a&gt;</description>
