Who is the false prophet?

What is the counterfeit trinity?

...The throne, of course, is Christ's throne, and it proclaims His sovereignty, His control over everything that comes to pass.

The sovereignty of God is the greatest of blessings to His children and the greatest of terrors to His enemies.  That is why unbelievers have always attacked it.  To deny His sovereignty is to deny God.  It is simply unbelief.

The Lord rules men and nations.  He rules the motions of the tiniest subatomic particles.

But many people say man, not God, is master of his &quot;fate.&quot;  This is what Satan wants you to believe.  He promised Eve that if she did what he wanted that she and all mankind &#8220;shall be as gods, knowing good and evil&#8221; (Gen. 3:5).  That's determining right and wrong for ourselves; being master of our &quot;fate.&quot;  But Scripture says this is a lie. (Isa. 45)

&#8220;There are many details in the doctrine of predestination, and each should be given its due weight; but the basic, the final, the ultimate answer to all objections is the relative positions of Creator and creature. All objections presuppose that man is in some way or other independent of God and has obtained from somewhere or achieved by his own efforts some rights over
against him. Obviously such a view is totally destructive of Christianity.&#8221;  (Dr. Gordon Clark, &quot;Predestination&quot;)</description>
