How are you saved?  Most people, even those who think of themselves as Christians, think that God essentially has a big balance scale, and when you die He piles up all the good things you've done on one side, all the bad on the other, and if it tips the right way you get into heaven.  But that's not found in the Bible.

Self-salvation comes naturally to us; thus it is the essence of all false religions.

But if you DO know the Gospel and believe in justification by faith alone, do you know the essence of the Christian life?  It's not so much a believer's living for Christ as it is Christ living IN the believer.</description>
