	<pubDate>Sat, 17 Apr 2010 00:32 GMT</pubDate>
	<link>http://www.sermonaudio.com/sermoninfo.asp?SID=416101923351</link>
	<guid>http://www.sermonaudio.com/sermoninfo.asp?SID=416101923351</guid>
	<author>James Evans</author>
	<category>Religion &amp; Spirituality</category>
	<enclosure length="24466911" url="http://mp3.sa-media.com/filearea/416101923351/416101923351.mp3" type="audio/mpeg"/>
	<itunes:subtitle>The Science Of The Flood - Genesis 6; Genesis 7-9</itunes:subtitle>
	<itunes:author>James Evans</itunes:author>
	<itunes:category text="Religion &amp; Spirituality"><itunes:category text="Christianity" /></itunes:category>
	<itunes:duration>51:00</itunes:duration>
	<itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit>
	<description>A new MP3 sermon from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.sermonaudio.com/source_detail.asp?sourceid=reformation&quot;&gt;Reformation Church&lt;/a&gt; is now available on SermonAudio.com with the following details:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Title:&lt;/b&gt; The Science Of The Flood&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Subtitle:&lt;/b&gt; The Science Of The Flood&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Speaker:&lt;/b&gt; James Evans&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Broadcaster:&lt;/b&gt; Reformation Church&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Event:&lt;/b&gt; Special Meeting&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Date:&lt;/b&gt; 4/11/2010&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Bible:&lt;/b&gt; Genesis 6; Genesis 7-9&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Length:&lt;/b&gt; 51 min. (64kbps)

&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;b&gt;Overview:&lt;/b&gt; The main modern sciences that show evidence of the Biblical flood are Geology, Archaeology, and Cryptozoology.

FLOOD PREDICTIONS&#8212;If the Flood caused the sedimentary rock strata, with their billions of fossils, then the following 13 points would be expected -- and, upon examination of the fossils in the strata &#8212; they all prove true...

...HOW DO FOSSILS TESTIFY TO THE FLOOD?  A great Flood -- the one described in the Bible in Genesis 6 to 9 --rapidly covered the earth with water. When it did, sediments of pebbles, gravel, clay, and sand were laid down in successive strata, covering animal and plant life. Under great pressure, these sediments turned into what we today call &quot;sedimentary rock.&quot; All that mass of water-laid material successively covered millions of living creatures. The result is fossils, which today are only found in the sedimentary rock strata.

When the Flood overwhelmed the world, the first to be covered were slow-moving animals, the next to be covered were somewhat larger, somewhat faster-moving animals, and so it went. Today we can dig into these rock strata and find that the lowest stratum tends to have the slowest-moving creatures; above them are faster ones. Evolutionist scientists declare these lowest strata are many millions of years old (570 million for the oldest, the Cambrian), and the topmost to be the most recent (the Pliocene at 10 million, and the Pleistocene at 2 million years).

But, in actuality, we will discover that the evidence indicates that all the sedimentary strata with their hoards of fossils were laid down within a very short time.</description>
</item>
