&lt;b&gt;Length:&lt;/b&gt; 45 min. (32kbps)

&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;b&gt;Overview:&lt;/b&gt; What difference does your being a child of the Lord make in your life?  Have you ever really thought deeply about that question?  You&#8217;d be surprised (at least, I am) at the number of Christians who have to admit that no, they&#8217;ve never really focused on what difference their faith makes in their day-to-day living.

Here is another question to ponder:  Can you think of one thing you said or did yesterday that showed someone that you are a child of God in Christ?  That you have something that changes men&#8217;s hearts and changes the way they live?  There&#8217;s a question that has been repeated so often it&#8217;s become a cliche, but it&#8217;s so thought-provoking that even if you&#8217;ve heard it a hundred times it still should make you reflect:  If you were arrested for being a Christian, would there be enough evidence to convict you?

In what ways has your walk with the Lord changed you?  A lot?  A little? Or has it changed you at all?  If you think it has changed you, why do you think so?  How do you know?  Can others see the changes? We&#8217;ll call these differences some of the marks of a Christian.  This morning we&#8217;ll start to examine some of these marks.</description>
</item>
